as-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:23:18', '2022-10-02 08:23:18', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=253', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(254, 1, '2022-10-02 10:23:51', '2022-10-02 08:23:51', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the promentent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":192,"width":620,"height":216,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192" width="620" height="216"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#33456a;color:#ec9e3c">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#0f3d21;color:#ec9e3c">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:23:51', '2022-10-02 08:23:51', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=254', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` ( `ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(255, 1, '2022-10-02 10:24:19', '2022-10-02 08:24:19', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the promentent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":192,"width":620,"height":216,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192" width="620" height="216"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#33456a;color:#ec9e3c">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#0f3d21;color:#ec9e3c">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:24:19', '2022-10-02 08:24:19', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=255', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(256, 1, '2022-10-02 10:26:24', '2022-10-02 08:26:24', '', 'autobahn_lol', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'autobahn_lol', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:26:24', '2022-10-02 08:26:24', '', 188, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(257, 1, '2022-10-02 10:27:04', '2022-10-02 08:27:04', '', 'autostr@2x', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'autostr2x', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:27:04', '2022-10-02 08:27:04', '', 188, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(258, 1, '2022-10-02 10:29:27', '2022-10-02 08:29:27', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the promentent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":192,"width":620,"height":216,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192" width="620" height="216"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#33456a;color:#ec9e3c">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#0f3d21;color:#ec9e3c">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:29:27', '2022-10-02 08:29:27', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=258', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(259, 1, '2022-10-02 10:32:24', '2022-10-02 08:32:24', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the promentent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":192,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#33456a;color:#ec9e3c">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#0f3d21;color:#ec9e3c">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-231" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/detour.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Example of additional explination sign. Text should be in the local language, for general and multipurpose signs in english and german.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:32:24', '2022-10-02 08:32:24', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=259', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(260, 1, '2022-10-02 10:35:37', '2022-10-02 08:35:37', '', 'Screen-Shot-2022-10-02-at-08.57.21', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'screen-shot-2022-10-02-at-08-57-21', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:35:37', '2022-10-02 08:35:37', '', 188, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screen-Shot-2022-10-02-at-08.57.21.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(261, 1, '2022-10-02 10:36:31', '2022-10-02 08:36:31', '', '2', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:36:31', '2022-10-02 08:36:31', '', 188, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/2.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(262, 1, '2022-10-02 10:36:32', '2022-10-02 08:36:32', '', '1', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:36:32', '2022-10-02 08:36:32', '', 188, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/1.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0) ;
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` ( `ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(263, 1, '2022-10-02 10:40:32', '2022-10-02 08:40:32', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§1. Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the promentent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§2. Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§3. Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§4. Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":192,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#33456a;color:#ec9e3c">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#0f3d21;color:#ec9e3c">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§5. Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§6. Color Coding</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To simplify intersections inside of cities, a special color coding is used, whereby each possible direction (excluding U-Turns/turning around) is labled with a color.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 1 (§1)</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 2 (§2)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-262" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-261" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/2.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bottom before-intersection signs (replaces 5.2.a, variant 1 &amp; 2) are not always used. The replacements are known as 6.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>7. Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-231" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/detour.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Example of additional explination sign. Text should be in the local language, for general and multipurpose signs in english and german.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overview on road markings &amp; in-game objects coming soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:40:32', '2022-10-02 08:40:32', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=263', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(264, 1, '2022-10-02 10:42:53', '2022-10-02 08:42:53', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§1. Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the promentent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§2. Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§3. Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§4. Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":192,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#33456a;color:#ec9e3c">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#0f3d21;color:#ec9e3c">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§5. Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§6. Color Coding</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To simplify intersections inside of cities, a special color coding is used, whereby each possible direction (excluding U-Turns/turning around) is labled with a color.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 1 (§1)</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 2 (§2)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-262" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-261" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/2.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption>Arrow signs -> §6.1.a, §6.2.a, Before-intersection signs -> §6.1.b, §6.2.b</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bottom before-intersection signs, 6.1.b &amp; 6.2.b, (replaces 5.2.a, variant 1 &amp; 2) are not always used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The arrow signs take the place of 5.1.a</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Color coding can only be used on side roads.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>§7. Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-231" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/detour.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Example of additional explination sign. Text should be in the local language, for general and multipurpose signs in english and german.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overview on road markings &amp; in-game objects coming soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:42:53', '2022-10-02 08:42:53', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=264', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(265, 1, '2022-10-02 10:55:30', '2022-10-02 08:55:30', '', '4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '4', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:55:30', '2022-10-02 08:55:30', '', 21, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/4.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(267, 1, '2022-10-02 10:56:19', '2022-10-02 08:56:19', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">The Taeko &amp; Co Archive</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:search {"label":"","placeholder":"Seach Taeko \\u0026 Co...","buttonText":"Search"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:post-featured-image {"align":"wide"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back in 2020, Taeko &amp; Co was just a Minecraft server. Now it\'s more of a broad name of a lot of different projects done by myself (taeko) and my friend Lprd245, as well as many of our other friends. This website is our place online to publish and save those projects. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '21-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:56:19', '2022-10-02 08:56:19', '', 21, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=267', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(269, 1, '2022-10-02 10:57:35', '2022-10-02 08:57:35', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">The Taeko &amp; Co Archive</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:search {"label":"","placeholder":"Seach Taeko \\u0026 Co...","buttonText":"Search"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":265,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/4-1024x551.png" alt="" class="wp-image-265"/><figcaption>An old, ca. early 2021 birds eye view of Machinaka, Atami</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back in 2020, Taeko &amp; Co was just a Minecraft server. Now it\'s more of a broad name of a lot of different projects done by myself (taeko) and my friend Lprd245, as well as many of our other friends. This website is our place online to publish and save those projects. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '21-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-02 10:57:35', '2022-10-02 08:57:35', '', 21, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=269', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
