(322, 1, '2022-12-12 19:40:09', '2022-12-12 18:40:09', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="has-text-align-center">A History of T&amp;C Logos</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Taeko &amp; Co\'s two and a half years, we\'ve gone through a few iterations of logos, each time being updated to better reflect the entire project.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every logo has been made "in house", including the latest logo, a proud product of the Grafik Dsign Club.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Taeko &amp; Co\'s Current Logo, 12th December 2022</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":317,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/tc_logo.png" alt="" class="wp-image-317"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Proudly produced by the GDC (Grafik Dsign Club), this logo is T&amp;C\'s trendy new look. As is a recurring theme in each design, the main drawn element is the Atami Radio Tower, a tradition since the very first logo.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our name is now stylized elegantly &amp; simply "taeko&amp;co.", which is complimented by a heavy typeface, inspired by advertisements and posters of the 70\'s and 80\'s. The waves add a dynamic feeling to the logo.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November - December 2022</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":313,"width":462,"height":472,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/TCLOGO.png" alt="" class="wp-image-313" width="462" height="472"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pixel-y design was conceived on the creative test server unintentionally. It looked good enough, that it was decided it should be drawn up "properly". Soon after, it replaced Taeko &amp; Co\'s aging old logo.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>September 2021 - November 2022</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":270,"width":504,"height":438,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screen-Shot-2022-10-02-at-11.01.34.png" alt="" class="wp-image-270" width="504" height="438"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most of this logo is defined by new developments of the late 2021 server, namely the Atami-Atocha train station and the Lyria Tower. Additionally, an ice road was added, symbolizing the exploding expansion of ice paved roads on the server.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 2020 - September 2021</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":323,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/taeko_and_co_logo-1024x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-323"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taeko &amp; Co\'s first proper logo. Intended for the planned T-Shirts of that year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>September - November 2020</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":324,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/taekotachi-1024x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-324"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taeko &amp; Co\'s first logo, after being renamed from RMC (Retarded Minecrafters), intended to be temporary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'A History of T&C Logos', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-history-of-tc-logos', '', '', '2022-12-12 19:42:26', '2022-12-12 18:42:26', '', 0, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=322', 0, 'post', '', 0),
