(396, 1, '2023-05-30 14:05:34', '2023-05-30 12:05:34', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Good design resonates with us...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Design is, and always has been, at the forefront of everything we do. We believe that good, beautiful design comes hand in hand with flawless functionality, especially in the age of increasingly complex and frustratingly buggy software that is supposed to make our lives easier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taeko &amp; Co. stands for meaningful, subtle, accessible and functional design. We see the beauty in towering concrete infrastructure, sleek glass high rises, modern expressive buildings, state-of-the-art tunnels and concise signage. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you see beauty in those examples too, consider looking through our portfolio to get inspired, or maybe even contacting us about potential commissions. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Portfolio</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":317,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/tc_logo.png" alt="" class="wp-image-317"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Taeko &amp; Co. Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our logo of course takes the first place in our portfolio. It is a proud collaboration between members of T&amp;C and pays homage to previous logos. The heavy typeface and waviness express our identity as a free, independent design collective. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":391,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/discordlogotc.png" alt="" class="wp-image-391"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Icon of T&amp;C Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":392,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/chaffeur_psd_en.png" alt="" class="wp-image-392"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Chauffeur Transpassodome, </strong>poster for the Passodome ANR line on server</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":393,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-13.47.07-684x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-393"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":394,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-13.45.50-1024x762.png" alt="" class="wp-image-394"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Road signs for Atteca &amp; Swarovski</strong>, see <a href="https://taeko-and-co.ch/index.php/2022/10/02/signalization-on-attecan-roads/" data-type="post" data-id="188">detailed development analysis</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":395,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/milchbuck-1024x724.png" alt="" class="wp-image-395"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Poster for Milchbuck Tunnel in Zurich</strong>, including colorized image from ETH Archives</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Design', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '347-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:05:34', '2023-05-30 12:05:34', '', 347, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=396', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(397, 1, '2023-05-30 14:06:42', '2023-05-30 12:06:42', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Update May 2023 : Many standards on this page have since been updated or replaced. This page is in the process of being rewritten, but will remain online as-is until then.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§1. Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the prominent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§2. Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§3. Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§4. Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":192,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="color:#ec9e3c;background-color:#33456a">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="color:#ec9e3c;background-color:#0f3d21">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§5. Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§6. Color Coding</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To simplify intersections inside of cities, a special color coding is used, whereby each possible direction (excluding U-Turns/turning around) is labled with a color.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 1 (§1)</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 2 (§2)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-262" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-261" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/2.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Arrow signs -&gt; §6.1.a, §6.2.a, Before-intersection signs -&gt; §6.1.b, §6.2.b</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bottom before-intersection signs, 6.1.b &amp; 6.2.b, (replaces 5.2.a, variant 1 &amp; 2) are not always used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The arrow signs take the place of 5.1.a</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Color coding can only be used on side roads.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§7. Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-231" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/detour.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Example of additional explination sign. Text should be in the local language, for general and multipurpose signs in english and german.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overview on road markings &amp; in-game objects coming soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:06:42', '2023-05-30 12:06:42', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=397', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` ( `ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(398, 1, '2023-05-30 14:06:47', '2023-05-30 12:06:47', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads (Old)</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Update May 2023 : Many standards on this page have since been updated or replaced. This page is in the process of being rewritten, but will remain online as-is until then.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§1. Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the prominent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§2. Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§3. Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§4. Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":192,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="color:#ec9e3c;background-color:#33456a">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="color:#ec9e3c;background-color:#0f3d21">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§5. Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§6. Color Coding</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To simplify intersections inside of cities, a special color coding is used, whereby each possible direction (excluding U-Turns/turning around) is labled with a color.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 1 (§1)</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 2 (§2)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-262" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-261" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/2.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Arrow signs -&gt; §6.1.a, §6.2.a, Before-intersection signs -&gt; §6.1.b, §6.2.b</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bottom before-intersection signs, 6.1.b &amp; 6.2.b, (replaces 5.2.a, variant 1 &amp; 2) are not always used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The arrow signs take the place of 5.1.a</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Color coding can only be used on side roads.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§7. Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-231" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/detour.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Example of additional explination sign. Text should be in the local language, for general and multipurpose signs in english and german.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overview on road markings &amp; in-game objects coming soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-autosave-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:06:47', '2023-05-30 12:06:47', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=398', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(399, 1, '2023-05-30 14:06:52', '2023-05-30 12:06:52', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Signalization on Attecan Roads (Old)</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Update May 2023 : Many standards on this page have since been updated or replaced. This page is in the process of being rewritten, but will remain online as-is until then.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§1. Preword</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of road signalization is to guarantee easy and correct usage of roadways. A well designed system is easy to understand and to learn. Atteca\'s road signage has undergone many updates since roads were first introduced in October of 2020. Now, as boats are taking the prominent role in short to medium distance travel, good signage is more important than ever. For this reason, Lprd245 &amp; I are reforming the signage, based on the early 2022 reform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§2. Typeface</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The typeface used for all signs is the SNV (Schweizerische Normenverein) font. It features concise, modern and ledgible characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For signs where only numbers are displayed, a modified &amp; custom version of the Swiss Licence Plate font is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§3. Units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meters (= length of 1 block) are used for all distance measurements. This is because blocks have a major shortcoming, that is that the diagonal of the block is equal to <code>sqrt(2)</code> blocks. When using blocks (blk), the distance is counted as the amount of blocks (for example in building) needed to complete the distance. Therefore, depending on the direction, the actual objective length in meters (m) may be different.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§4. Colors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Colors are important in aiding the readablity of signs. Atteca adapts these 3 general, base color schemes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"wide","id":192,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Artboard-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-192"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Side Roads &amp; General Signage : #fff, #000, #000</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#33456a","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="color:#ec9e3c;background-color:#33456a">Main Roads : #33456A, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"background":"#0f3d21","text":"#ec9e3c"}}} -->\n<p class="has-text-color has-background" style="color:#ec9e3c;background-color:#0f3d21">Expressways : #0F3D21, #fff, #EC9E3C</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§5. Directional Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An overview of directional signs in the following table.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide","className":"is-style-regular"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide is-style-regular"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§a. Side Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§b. Main Roads</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">§c. Expressways</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§1. In/At Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-195" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_side.png" alt=""><br>see "color coding" section</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-196" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main.png" alt=""><br>Standard intersection<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br>Level seperated intersections</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-199" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_atb.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-197" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/in_main_2.png" alt=""><br><img class="wp-image-212" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§2. Before Intersection</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-202" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-203" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_side1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-206" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main1.png" alt=""><br>Variant 1<br><img class="wp-image-205" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bef_main.png" alt=""><br>Variant 2</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-207" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_einspuren.png" alt=""><br>Splitting of Expressways<br><img class="wp-image-208" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/atb_exit.png" alt=""><br>Expressway Exit</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§3 .Intersection Announcement</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2a </td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable, use 2b</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-210" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/announce_atb.png" alt=""><br>Exit Announcement, usually 500m before</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">§4. Distance Tables</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Not Applicable</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-213" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel_main.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-214" style="width: 200px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/distance_tafel.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other types of directional signs may be created if needed, but an effort should be made to stick to the conventions above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§6. Color Coding</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To simplify intersections inside of cities, a special color coding is used, whereby each possible direction (excluding U-Turns/turning around) is labled with a color.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 1 (§1)</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Variant 2 (§2)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-262" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-261" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/2.png" alt=""></td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Arrow signs -&gt; §6.1.a, §6.2.a, Before-intersection signs -&gt; §6.1.b, §6.2.b</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bottom before-intersection signs, 6.1.b &amp; 6.2.b, (replaces 5.2.a, variant 1 &amp; 2) are not always used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The arrow signs take the place of 5.1.a</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Color coding can only be used on side roads.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">§7. Warning &amp; Information Signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {"hasFixedLayout":true,"align":"wide"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-table alignwide"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Sign</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Description &amp; Usage</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-222" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/speedlimit2022.1.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Speed Limits/Recommendations<br>The limit should be set so that it does not change very much. In a city, the base limit is 50 km/h, outside of a city it is 100 km/h, and on expressways it is 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-219" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/fussganger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Pedestrian Crossing<br>Usually accompanied by orange/white marking on the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-221" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/reiter.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Horse Traffic Crossing<br>Where horse and boat traffic is seperated and must cross, this sign indicates the crossing.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-229" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/bend_leftnew.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-251" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/wavy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Bend in direction of arrow<br>Can be accompanied by yellow blocks on the side of the road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-243" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-242" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/narrows_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Narrowing of road</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-250" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/traffic_from_left.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic merging from side</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-249" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/other_danger.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Other warning<br>Accompanied by sign explaining danger, usually construction</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-225" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/ampel.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic control light, arrows showing location of danger/warning</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-245" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/oncoming.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Traffic returns to two way after one way zone. Keep left.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-248" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/snow.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Snow may cover roadway. Only used on blue ice paved roads.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-240" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-241" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/lights_mand_end.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Manditory usage of lighting, if player is using optifine</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-246" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/open_lane.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-233" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closing_left.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-232" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/closed_lane.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Lane usage indicators.<br>Green = Open<br>Yellow = Move in direction<br>Red X = Closed, do not use<br>Used often in tunnels to simplify driving lanes</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-236" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/kreisverkehr.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Roundabout</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-226" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_45_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-234" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/arrow_90_new.png" alt=""><img class="wp-image-227" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/chevron.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Mandatory direction. Yellow/red chevron indicates road edge.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-237" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/giveway.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Give way to traffic on intersecting road.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-230" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/derestrict.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">End of restrictions. Overtaking &amp; standard speed limit are permitted.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-224" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/parkieren-copy.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Parking area</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-256" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autobahn_lol.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with at least 2 lanes per direction. Speed limit 120 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-257" style="width: 500px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/autostr@2x.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Begin/End Expressway with less than 2 lanes per direction or unsegregated directions. Speed limit 100 km/h.</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><img class="wp-image-231" style="width: 150px;" src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/detour.png" alt=""></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Example of additional explination sign. Text should be in the local language, for general and multipurpose signs in english and german.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overview on road markings &amp; in-game objects coming soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Signalization on Attecan Roads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:06:52', '2023-05-30 12:06:52', '', 188, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=399', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(400, 1, '2023-05-30 14:07:18', '2023-05-30 12:07:18', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Good design resonates with us...</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Design is, and always has been, at the forefront of everything we do. We believe that good, beautiful design comes hand in hand with flawless functionality, especially in the age of increasingly complex and frustratingly buggy software that is supposed to make our lives easier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taeko &amp; Co. stands for meaningful, subtle, accessible and functional design. We see the beauty in towering concrete infrastructure, sleek glass high rises, modern expressive buildings, state-of-the-art tunnels and concise signage. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you see beauty in those examples too, consider looking through our portfolio to get inspired, or maybe even contacting us about potential commissions. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Portfolio</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":317,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/tc_logo.png" alt="" class="wp-image-317"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Taeko &amp; Co. Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our logo of course takes the first place in our portfolio. It is a proud collaboration between members of T&amp;C and pays homage to previous logos. The heavy typeface and waviness express our identity as a free, independent design collective. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":391,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/discordlogotc.png" alt="" class="wp-image-391"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Icon of T&amp;C Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":392,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/chaffeur_psd_en.png" alt="" class="wp-image-392"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Chauffeur Transpassodome, </strong>poster for the Passodome ANR line on server</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":393,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-13.47.07-684x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-393"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":394,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-13.45.50-1024x762.png" alt="" class="wp-image-394"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Road signs for Atteca &amp; Swarovski</strong>, see <a href="https://taeko-and-co.ch/index.php/2022/10/02/signalization-on-attecan-roads/" data-type="post" data-id="188">detailed development analysis</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":395,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/milchbuck-1024x724.png" alt="" class="wp-image-395"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Poster for Milchbuck Tunnel in Zurich</strong>, including colorized image from ETH Archives</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Design', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '347-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:07:18', '2023-05-30 12:07:18', '', 347, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=400', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(401, 1, '2023-05-30 14:09:14', '2023-05-30 12:09:14', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Good design resonates with us...</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Design is, and always has been, at the forefront of everything we do. We believe that good, beautiful design comes hand in hand with flawless functionality, especially in the age of increasingly complex and frustratingly buggy software that is supposed to make our lives easier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taeko &amp; Co. stands for meaningful, subtle, accessible and functional design. We see the beauty in towering concrete infrastructure, sleek glass high rises, modern expressive buildings, state-of-the-art tunnels and concise signage. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you see beauty in those examples too, consider looking through our portfolio to get inspired, or maybe even contacting us about potential commissions. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Portfolio</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":317,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/tc_logo.png" alt="" class="wp-image-317"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Taeko &amp; Co. Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our logo of course takes the first place in our portfolio. It is a proud collaboration between members of T&amp;C and pays homage to previous logos. The heavy typeface and waviness express our identity as a free, independent design collective. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":391,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/discordlogotc.png" alt="" class="wp-image-391"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Icon of T&amp;C Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":392,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/chaffeur_psd_en.png" alt="" class="wp-image-392"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Chauffeur Transpassodome, </strong>poster for the Passodome ANR line on server</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":394,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-13.45.50-1024x762.png" alt="" class="wp-image-394"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Road signs for Atteca &amp; Swarovski</strong>, see <a href="https://taeko-and-co.ch/index.php/2022/10/02/signalization-on-attecan-roads/" data-type="post" data-id="188">detailed development analysis</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":395,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/milchbuck-1024x724.png" alt="" class="wp-image-395"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Poster for Milchbuck Tunnel in Zurich</strong>, including colorized image from ETH Archives</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Design', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '347-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:09:14', '2023-05-30 12:09:14', '', 347, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=401', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(402, 1, '2023-05-30 14:10:52', '2023-05-30 12:10:52', '', 'Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-14.10.16', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'screenshot-2023-05-30-at-14-10-16', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:10:52', '2023-05-30 12:10:52', '', 347, 'http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-14.10.16.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(403, 1, '2023-05-30 14:11:06', '2023-05-30 12:11:06', '<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Good design resonates with us...</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Design is, and always has been, at the forefront of everything we do. We believe that good, beautiful design comes hand in hand with flawless functionality, especially in the age of increasingly complex and frustratingly buggy software that is supposed to make our lives easier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taeko &amp; Co. stands for meaningful, subtle, accessible and functional design. We see the beauty in towering concrete infrastructure, sleek glass high rises, modern expressive buildings, state-of-the-art tunnels and concise signage. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you see beauty in those examples too, consider looking through our portfolio to get inspired, or maybe even contacting us about potential commissions. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Portfolio</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":317,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="http://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/tc_logo.png" alt="" class="wp-image-317"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Taeko &amp; Co. Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our logo of course takes the first place in our portfolio. It is a proud collaboration between members of T&amp;C and pays homage to previous logos. The heavy typeface and waviness express our identity as a free, independent design collective. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":391,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/discordlogotc.png" alt="" class="wp-image-391"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Icon of T&amp;C Logo</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":392,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/chaffeur_psd_en.png" alt="" class="wp-image-392"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Chauffeur Transpassodome, </strong>poster for the Passodome ANR line on server</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":394,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-13.45.50-1024x762.png" alt="" class="wp-image-394"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Road signs for Atteca &amp; Swarovski</strong>, see <a href="https://taeko-and-co.ch/index.php/2022/10/02/signalization-on-attecan-roads/" data-type="post" data-id="188">detailed development analysis</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":395,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/milchbuck-1024x724.png" alt="" class="wp-image-395"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Poster for Milchbuck Tunnel in Zurich</strong>, including colorized image from ETH Archives</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":402,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://taeko-and-co.ch/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Screenshot-2023-05-30-at-14.10.16-1024x485.png" alt="" class="wp-image-402"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Attecan National Railways</strong>, branding/logo</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Design', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '347-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-30 14:11:06', '2023-05-30 12:11:06', '', 347, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=403', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(404, 1, '2023-06-01 12:41:29', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->\n<h1 class="wp-block-heading">Road Standards for Atteca &amp; Swarovski - an Overview</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Roads represent the most accessible and widespread transport solution on Taeko &amp; Co. New roads are added to the masterplan almost weekly. For navigating the complex network successfully, signals and signs are instrumental. This page gives a comprehensive overview of the signs, signals and planning standards for Swarovski and Attecan roads.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Masterplan</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Masterplan is the central orientation for the development of the (inter-)national road network. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Road Standards for Atteca &amp; Swarovski - an Overview', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2023-06-01 12:41:29', '2023-06-01 10:41:29', '', 0, 'https://taeko-and-co.ch/?p=404', 0, 'post', '', 0) ;
